thread.title: J&J starts clinical trial of Ebola vaccine in Sierra Leone
thread.title_full: J&J starts clinical trial of Ebola vaccine in Sierra Leone | Reuters

author: Reuters
title: J&J starts clinical trial of Ebola vaccine in Sierra Leone
text:
Oct 9 Johnson & Johnson said it has begun a safety and immunogenicity clinical trial of a preventive Ebola vaccine regimen in Sierra Leone.
Trial recruitment is underway and the first volunteers have received their initial vaccine dose, the company said in a statement.
This is the first study conducted of Janssen's Ebola prime-boost vaccine regimen in a West African country affected by the recent Ebola epidemic, J&J said. (Reporting by Supriya Kurane in Bengaluru; Editing by Anupama Dwivedi)
